      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Project requirements state that the QOI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly traceable to the clinical endpoint of plasma-free hemoglobin elevation.",
      "rationale": "NIH is used as the primary QOI and is clinically accepted, but the mapping from NIH to plasma-free hemoglobin elevation under chronic VAD conditions has not been formally established for this device geometry. Achieved level 3."
    },
